# Dominat8 Build Continuity

Use this when continuing work on the Dominat8.io AI website builder so the build stays consistent with the existing design and conventions.

## What This Project Is

- **Dominat8**: AI that generates a **complete, single-page website** as one self-contained HTML file from a user prompt + industry.
- **Flow**: User enters prompt + industry → streaming generation via `/api/io/generate` → preview in iframe → optional deploy.
- **Branch context**: `claude/complete-website-designs-YqxQ4` introduced Phase 1 real AI builder, security fixes, and error handling. Continue in that vein.

## Key Paths

- **Builder UI**: `src/io/surfaces/Builder.tsx` — main builder (industries, prompts, typewriter, preview iframe, deploy).
- **App entry**: `src/app/page.tsx` renders `<Builder />`; `src/app/io/page.tsx` renders TV shell (`IOTVShell`).
- **Generation API**: `src/app/api/io/generate/route.ts` — edge, streaming, single HTML output.
- **Proxy**: `src/proxy.ts` — Clerk auth + route protection, custom domain rewrite, /io rewrite; avoid breaking host/rewrite behavior.

## Generation Contract (Do Not Weaken)

The generate route’s system prompt defines the product. Output must remain:

- **Single self-contained HTML** — no markdown, no external CSS except Google Fonts, minimal inline JS.
- **Sections required**: Nav, Hero (headline + CTA), Features/Services (3–6), Social proof or Stats, CTA section, Footer.
- **Quality bar**: Premium, modern, on-brand; real placeholder content (no Lorem ipsum); hand-crafted feel; strong typography and contrast.
- **SEO**: `<title>`, `<meta name="description">`, Open Graph tags.

When changing the generator: preserve these rules; only tighten or add optional enhancements.

## Conventions to Preserve

- **Security**: Iframe that shows generated HTML must use a strict sandbox. Do **not** add `allow-same-origin` together with `allow-scripts` (XSS risk). Validate `OPENAI_API_KEY` before using the OpenAI client.
- **Errors**: Generation failures must surface in the UI (no blank screen). Deploy button must have a real `onClick` handler and clear behavior.
- **Recovery**: Critical paths have BOOTSTRAP copies under `BOOTSTRAP/`; see `BOOTSTRAP/MANIFEST.md`. Fixes: replace the broken file with the BOOTSTRAP version (full replace, no patching).
- **Protected paths**: `docs/PROTECTED_PATHS.md` — avoid changing core routes/config without `[ALLOW-PROTECTED]` in the PR title when intentional.
- **Agents**: `agents/` hold spec modules (creative-director, conversion, SEO, proof, motion, etc.). Wiring is via API and KV; keep agent outputs and keys consistent.

## Stack

- Next.js (App Router), React, TypeScript.
- Generation: OpenAI (e.g. gpt-4o), streaming.
- Styling: Tailwind where used; generated sites are inline CSS in HTML.

## How to “Build Like Claude” Here

- Prefer small, focused commits and clear fix descriptions (e.g. “Fix: Error state has no UI when API generation fails”).
- Keep the bar: premium output, safe iframe, visible errors, working deploy.
- When adding features, align with existing patterns in `Builder.tsx` and the generate route (industries, prompts, streaming, state).
- Do not remove or relax security measures added in the Claude branch (sandbox, API key checks).
